<doc id="1190817" wikidata="Q654954" url="?curid=1190817" title="Futaro Yamada">
<text>was the pen name of , a Japanese author.
He was born in Yabu, Hyogo.
In 1947, he wrote a mystery short story and was awarded a prize by the magazine .
He was discovered by Edogawa Rampo and became a novelist.
He wrote many ninja (忍法帖 &quot;Ninpōchō&quot; series) and mystery stories. Many of his works have been adapted for film, TV, manga, and anime.

