<doc id="1190958" wikidata="Q8075990" url="?curid=1190958" title="Zyzzogeton">
<text>Zyzzogeton is a rare genus of leafhoppers endemic to South America. It is named after a former genus &quot;Zyzza&quot; (probably an onomatopoeia), appended with the ancient Greek &quot;geitōn&quot; ( &#x27;neighbour&#x27;).

The word is known for being the last word defined in the &quot;Webster&#x27;s New International Dictionary, Unabridged&quot; released in September 1961. It also appears in the 1939 Second edition, and is still present in current versions.

