<doc id="1191041" wikidata="Q55643022" url="?curid=1191041" title="Extended supersymmetry">
<text>In theoretical physics, extended supersymmetry is supersymmetry whose infinitesimal generators formula_1 carry not only a spinor index formula_2, but also an additional index formula_3 where formula_4 is integer (such as 2 or 4).

Extended supersymmetry is also called formula_5, formula_6 supersymmetry, for example. Extended supersymmetry is very important for analysis of mathematical properties of quantum field theory and superstring theory. The more extended supersymmetry is, the more it constrains physical observables and parameters.

==See also==
* Supersymmetry algebra
* Harmonic superspace
* Projective superspace

