===== Time-domain notes=====

* The Lorenz gauge condition is satisfied:
: formula_51
* The position of formula_42, the point at which values for formula_3 and formula_2 are found, only enters the equation as part of the scalar distance from formula_46 to formula_56 The direction from formula_46 to formula_58 does not enter into the equation. The only thing that matters about a source point is how far away it is.
* The integrand uses &quot;retarded time&quot;, formula_45 This reflects the fact that changes in the sources propagate at the speed of light. Hence the charge and current densities affecting the electric and magnetic potential at formula_42 and formula_43, from remote location formula_62 must also be at some prior time formula_63
* The equation for formula_2 is a vector equation. In Cartesian coordinates, the equation separates into three scalar equations: formula_65 In this form it is apparent that the component of formula_2 in a given direction depends only on the components of formula_67 that are in the same direction. If the current is carried in a straight wire, formula_2 points in the same direction as the wire.

