===== Frequency domain notes =====

There are a few notable things about formula_2 and formula_3 calculated in this way:
* The Lorenz gauge condition is satisfied: formula_81 This implies that the frequency domain electric potential, formula_3, can be computed entirely from the current density distribution, formula_40.
* The position of formula_84 the point at which values for formula_3 and formula_2 are found, only enters the equation as part of the scalar distance from formula_46 to formula_88 The direction from formula_46 to formula_42 does not enter into the equation. The only thing that matters about a source point is how far away it is.
* The integrand uses the phase shift term formula_91 which plays a role equivalent to &quot;retarded time&quot;. This reflects the fact that changes in the sources propagate at the speed of light; propagation delay in the time domain is equivalent to a phase shift in the frequency domain. 
* The equation for formula_2 is a vector equation. In Cartesian coordinates, the equation separates into three scalar equations: formula_93 In this form it is apparent that the component of formula_2 in a given direction depends only on the components of formula_95 that are in the same direction. If the current is carried in a straight wire, formula_2 points in the same direction as the wire.

